3.22

*Conditional Clauses*
sī, nisi (dum, dummodo, modo)

see mood and tense for type of conditional

  FUT   sī + fut ind, fut ind     sī + pres subj, pres subj
  PRES  sī + pres ind, pres ind   sī + impf subj, impf subj
  PAST  sī + past ind, past ind   sī + pluperf subj, pluperf subj

future conditional (Future Less Vivid): something less sure, more abstract, more possible instead of sure
present subjunctive (Contrary to Fact): things that could/would happen in the present but aren't
past subjunctive (Contrary to Fact): see above
